The membership of the Personnel Steering Committee shall be appointed by the Governor and shall consist of:
Two (2) members from the Governor's Commission on Quality and Efficiency established by Executive Order 93-282. At least one (1) of these members shall also be a member of the Career Service System Task Force created by Executive Order 93-1139;
Two (2) members from private industry, at least one of whom shall also be a member of Career Service System Task Force;
One (1) employee with status who has at least ten (10) years of experience in an Executive Department agency other than the Personnel Cabinet;
One (1) employee with status in a management classification in an Executive Department agency other than the Personnel Cabinet;
Two (2) Personnel Cabinet employees with status who have personnel system experience; and
One (1) member who is either a member of the Personnel Board, or a member of its staff.
